<paragraph id="8BAA431C5C13FFFEFF52F8B2FEE6F56D" blockId="3.[189,334,1792,1818]" box="[189,334,1792,1818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="D0E2F4705C13FFFEFF52F8B2FEE6F56D" bold="true" box="[189,334,1792,1818]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C13FFFEFF52F8B2FEE6F56D" bold="true" box="[189,334,1792,1818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA431C5C13FFFEFF52F89DFE15F53F" blockId="3.[189,445,1838,1865]" box="[189,445,1838,1865]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">BODY. Medium-sized.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA431C5C13FFFEFF52F8C3FADEF5DA" blockId="3.[189,1399,1904,1966]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
HEAD. Fastigium verticis with two conical tubercles, apices obtusely rounded, pointing forward (
<figureCitation id="132E5F995C13FFFEFF29F821FE8FF5DA" box="[198,295,1939,1965]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[191,234,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatachycines pentus gen. et sp. nov. A–F. Holotype, ♂ (HBU). A–C. Head and pronotum. A. Frontal view. B. Lateral view. C. Dorsal view. D–F. Apex of abdomen. D. Lateral view. E. Dorsal view. F. Ventral view. G–H. Paratype, ♀ (HBU). G. Subgenital plate in ventral view. H. Ovipositor in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517879" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517879/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Eyes ovoid, protruding forward; median ocellus oval, located between antennal sockets;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA431C5C14FFF9FF52FEBBFABCF331" blockId="4.[189,1399,265,327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
lateral ocelli circular, situated on lateral margins of basal fastigium verticis (
<figureCitation id="132E5F995C14FFF9FB68FEBBFAB8F354" box="[1159,1296,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[191,234,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatachycines pentus gen. et sp. nov. A–F. Holotype, ♂ (HBU). A–C. Head and pronotum. A. Frontal view. B. Lateral view. C. Dorsal view. D–F. Apex of abdomen. D. Lateral view. E. Dorsal view. F. Ventral view. G–H. Paratype, ♀ (HBU). G. Subgenital plate in ventral view. H. Ovipositor in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517879" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517879/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 2A–B</figureCitation>
). Apical segment of maxillary palpus distinctly longer than subapical segment, apex inflated, globular.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA431C5C14FFF8FF52FEDCFBA5F381" blockId="4.[189,1401,366,603]" lastBlockId="5.[189,1399,265,503]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
THORAX. Pronotum long, anterior margin straight, posterior margin arcuate; lateral lobe longer than high, ventral margin arc-shaped (
<figureCitation id="132E5F995C14FFF9FDA1FE23FD79F3DC" box="[590,721,401,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[191,234,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatachycines pentus gen. et sp. nov. A–F. Holotype, ♂ (HBU). A–C. Head and pronotum. A. Frontal view. B. Lateral view. C. Dorsal view. D–F. Apex of abdomen. D. Lateral view. E. Dorsal view. F. Ventral view. G–H. Paratype, ♀ (HBU). G. Subgenital plate in ventral view. H. Ovipositor in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517879" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517879/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 2B–C</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum and metanotum short, posterior margin of mesonotum arcuate, posterior margin of metanotum straight. Fore coxa with one small spine; inner margin of fore femur with 11–12 spines on ventral surface, internal genicular lobe with one small spine, external genicular lobe with one long spine; fore tibia with one inner spine and two outer spines on ventral surface, apex with one pair of dorsal spines and one pair of ventral spines, between paired ventral spines with one small spine. Middle femur unarmed on ventral surface, internal and external genicular lobes each with one long spine; middle tibia with one inner spine and one outer spine on ventral surface, apex with one pair of dorsal spines and one pair of ventral spines, between paired ventral spines with one small spine. Hind femur with 7–10 inner spines on ventral surface, internal genicular lobe with one spine, external genicular lobe unarmed; hind tibia with 72–83 inner spines and 70–80 outer spines on dorsal surface, with one pair of dorsal spines in subapical area, and at apex with one pair of dorsal spines and two pairs of ventral spines, interno-dorsal spine markedly longer than hind basitarsus; hind basitarsus with one apical spine on dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6A13945C14FFF9FF50F8D6FEE5F59F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517879" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6517879" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517879/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" startId="4.[191,234,1892,1918]" targetBox="[189,1398,684,1854]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BAA431C5C14FFF9FF50F8D6FEE5F59F" blockId="4.[190,1399,1892,2024]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FF50F8D6FEA6F508" bold="true" box="[191,270,1892,1919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C15389F5C14FFF9FEF9F8D7FD83F508" authority="Zhu &amp; Shi &amp; Zhou, 2022" authorityName="Zhu &amp; Shi &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2022" box="[278,555,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Megatachycines" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pentus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FEF9F8D7FD83F508" box="[278,555,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Megatachycines pentus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25222755C14FFF9FDDBF8D7FD42F508" box="[564,746,1893,1919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FD1AF8D6FC80F508" bold="true" box="[757,808,1892,1919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A–F</emphasis>
. Holotype, ♂ (HBU). 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FBD7F8D6FBD9F509" bold="true" box="[1080,1137,1892,1919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A–C</emphasis>
. Head and pronotum. 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FF50F83AFF7AF5D5" bold="true" box="[191,210,1928,1954]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A</emphasis>
. Frontal view. 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FE66F83AFE33F5D5" bold="true" box="[393,411,1928,1954]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">B</emphasis>
. Lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FDBFF83AFDCCF5D5" bold="true" box="[592,612,1928,1954]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
. Dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FCFBF83AFCE0F5D5" bold="true" box="[788,840,1928,1954]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">D–F</emphasis>
. Apex of abdomen. 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FBD2F83AFBF9F5D5" bold="true" box="[1085,1105,1928,1954]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">D</emphasis>
. Lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FAE9F83AFAB0F5D5" bold="true" box="[1286,1304,1928,1954]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">E</emphasis>
. Dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FEECF819FEBDF5B2" bold="true" box="[259,277,1963,1989]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">F</emphasis>
. Ventral view. 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FE27F819FDACF5B2" bold="true" box="[456,516,1963,1990]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">G–H</emphasis>
. Paratype, ♀ (HBU). 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FCE7F819FCB7F5B2" bold="true" box="[776,799,1963,1989]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">G</emphasis>
. Subgenital plate in ventral view. 
<emphasis id="B9619F0E5C14FFF9FB5AF819FB63F5B2" bold="true" box="[1205,1227,1963,1989]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">H</emphasis>
. Ovipositor in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BAA431C5C15FFFBFF52FDACFADEF331" blockId="5.[189,1399,542,603]" lastBlockId="6.[189,1398,265,327]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
MALE ABDOMEN. Posterior margins of all abdominal tergites without processes. Epiproct extended, pentagonal, posterior margin concave; paraproct simple, quadrangular in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="132E5F995C15FFF8FB0AFDF3FAC2F02C" box="[1253,1386,577,603]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[191,234,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatachycines pentus gen. et sp. nov. A–F. Holotype, ♂ (HBU). A–C. Head and pronotum. A. Frontal view. B. Lateral view. C. Dorsal view. D–F. Apex of abdomen. D. Lateral view. E. Dorsal view. F. Ventral view. G–H. Paratype, ♀ (HBU). G. Subgenital plate in ventral view. H. Ovipositor in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517879" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517879/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2D–E</figureCitation>
). Cercus slender, conical, apex acute (
<figureCitation id="132E5F995C16FFFBFD85FEBBFD61F354" box="[618,713,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[191,234,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatachycines pentus gen. et sp. nov. A–F. Holotype, ♂ (HBU). A–C. Head and pronotum. A. Frontal view. B. Lateral view. C. Dorsal view. D–F. Apex of abdomen. D. Lateral view. E. Dorsal view. F. Ventral view. G–H. Paratype, ♀ (HBU). G. Subgenital plate in ventral view. H. Ovipositor in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517879" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517879/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal sclerite of genitalia stilliform; dorso-lateral lobes distinctly sclerotized (
<figureCitation id="132E5F995C16FFFBFE2DFE9EFDECF330" box="[450,580,300,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,233,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,695,1890]" captionTargetId="figure-91@7.[189,1398,691,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 5. Male genitalia. A, C, E. Dorsal view. B, D, F. Ventral view. A–B. Megatachycines pentus gen. et sp. nov., paratype, ♂ (HBU). C–D. Megatachycines elongatus (Qin, Liu &amp; Li, 2017) comb. nov. E–F. Megatachycines trispinosus (Qin &amp; Li, 2020) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517910/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 5A–B</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate transverse and broad, apical area bilobed (
<figureCitation id="132E5F995C16FFFBFAE0FE9EFAC1F331" box="[1295,1385,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[191,234,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[189,1398,684,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatachycines pentus gen. et sp. nov. A–F. Holotype, ♂ (HBU). A–C. Head and pronotum. A. Frontal view. B. Lateral view. C. Dorsal view. D–F. Apex of abdomen. D. Lateral view. E. Dorsal view. F. Ventral view. G–H. Paratype, ♀ (HBU). G. Subgenital plate in ventral view. H. Ovipositor in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517879" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517879/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6A13945C15FFF8FF52F83AFA9CF59F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517891" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6517891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517891/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" startId="5.[189,232,1928,1954]" targetBox="[189,1398,694,1889]" targetPageId="5">
